es determined to maintain the apartheid-era status quo, and the grassroots efforts to effect social change.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGroup identityzSouth AfricazCape Town. 0aSociology, UrbanzSouth Africa. 4aAnthropology. 4aCultural & Social. 4aSocial Science. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aBesteman, Catherine, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025671240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094264640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520942646423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520942646/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles